## Emergency Triage Protocols

### TSI (Triage Severity Index) System

#### Triage Categories

| Category | Color Code | Wait Time | Clinical Criteria | Action Required |
|----------|------------|------------|-------------------|-----------------|
| **Immediate** | Red | 0 minutes | Life-threatening conditions | Immediate medical intervention |
| **Urgent** | Yellow | 15 minutes | Potentially serious conditions | Rapid assessment and treatment |
| **Delayed** | Green | 60 minutes | Non-life-threatening conditions | Standard medical care |
| **Expectant** | Black | Variable | Unlikely to survive | Comfort care only |

#### Triage Algorithm

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Patient Arrival] --> B{Airway Clear?}
    B -->|No| C[Immediate - Red]
    B -->|Yes| D{Breathing Normal?}
    D -->|No| C
    D -->|Yes| E{Circulation Adequate?}
    E -->|No| C
    E -->|Yes| F{Disability?}
    F -->|Severe| G[Urgent - Yellow]
    F -->|Mild| H{Pregnant/Elderly?}
    H -->|Yes| G
    H -->|No| I[Delayed - Green]
    
    C --> J[Immediate Treatment Area]
    G --> K[Urgent Treatment Area]
    I --> L[Delayed Treatment Area]
```

